States can move into each successive phase after establishing certain criteria, including documenting two weeks of declining case counts.
Instead of requiring states to hit a certain threshold of cases, the guidelines only ask states to show a "downward trajectory."
States are also instructed to use public health databases that are set up to track influenza-like symptoms.
He has another concern about the guidelines' minimalist approach to testing: "There are no targets, no goals.
Powers worries that the plan leaves a lot of open questions for states and doesn't define key terms.